Sophie Brandt https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sophie_Brandt 0 Sophie Brandt born Sophie Barth (July 4, 1876 – February 4, 1946) was an American actress and soprano singer of musical comedy, opera, and waltzes. She was "gifted with a voice capable of attaining unusually high notes," reported one magazine in 1904. She was known in private life as Mrs. William Burlock. She was born in St. Louis and died at Chicago in 1946.
